$a = random(1, 4, 1);
$b = random(5, 9, 1);    
$c = 2*$a + 3*$b;
$d = 2*$a;
$e = random(10, 30, 1);
$f = $e-2;
      
BEGIN_PGML
Here is a definition: [` x \: \Box \: y = 2x+3y `].  Read it and use it to:  
Find [` [$a] \: \Box \: [$b] \: =`] [____________]{Compute("$c")}

Find [`c \:\Box \: x \:= `] [_____________]{Compute("2*c+3*x")}

Solve for [`x`] if [`(x+1) \: \Box \: x = [$e]`]

[`x=`] [_____________]{Compute("$f/5")}
END_PGML

